Reasoning: The paper deals with the performance of codes over discrete memoryless channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on the Extrinsic Information Transfer (EXIT) chart, which is a tool used in the analysis of iterative decoding algorithms, such as turbo codes and concatenated codes, which are topics in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the implications of the results for different types of iterative receivers, which could fall under the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper mentions the treatment of the binary input additive white Gaussian noise channel, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
